tle><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/l0cHrns</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/NOB6Qic.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/l0cHrns</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[WerellnVileHero]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>How I met your mother.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/bFSxhz2</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/j9fQfve.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Fun stuff…send something tremendous.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/bFSxhz2</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[deafkitten]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Too true…</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/aoJKS9I</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eJD6uRW.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>So I live right next to the Galveston Bay, south east of Houston and this right here hits home.  

Recently Frontier has started construction in our city, to lay down and provide fiber for high speed Internet. Up until now, only Comcast XFinity was providing this service and they charged $134/mo for their service with no incentives, even for new customers.  Now Frontier is offering $64/mo and a $200 gift card to switch to them and Comcast is losing their shit.  

I’m not so naïve to think that corporations will be corporations and it’s just a power grab for them in the long run, but I for one like the competition and can appreciate my bills not being so high.  Just pisses me off that Comcast could have charged less for years but only now can “afford” to lower their prices.  

Welcome to America though, right?  End of rant…</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/aoJKS9I</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[wisher1977]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Family reunion</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/qxQF0Jk</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/KDspHjG.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/qxQF0Jk</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[anlyin]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Feel like this isn't being said enough...</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/pzXEq8S</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9aEMssm.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Feel free to post this on all of your back-woods family and friends' FB feeds.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/pzXEq8S</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[defunctdeity]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>$233.5 Million!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/YvnwDxq</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6T6c3S5.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/YvnwDxq</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[slotheroll]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Russian tank column eating shit and running scared</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/okDOMUj</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/LPmuovb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Apparently, today convoy of russian tanks bound for Kyiv got ambushed in city of...Brovary?...they ate lot of shit, heavy loses, commander ded.

